sql:
SELECT report_date
FROM pandemic_reports
WHERE region = 'Hubei';

SELECT DISTINCT region
FROM pandemic_reports
ORDER BY report_date, region;

SELECT SUM(confirmed_cases) AS total_confirmed_cases, AVG(vaccination_rate) AS average_vaccination_rate
FROM pandemic_reports
WHERE region = 'Hubei';

external_knowledge:
External knowledge: 
- 'most recent pandemic reports' refers to the reports with the highest level (i.e., the latest reports) in the recursive report hierarchy;
- The level of a report in the hierarchy corresponds to the distance from the starting reports (with report_id = 0 or 1);
- The reports are ordered chronologically based on their report_date.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT region
FROM pandemic_reports
ORDER BY region;

SELECT DISTINCT report_date, region
FROM pandemic_reports
ORDER BY report_date, region;
